Avis Europe, Glencore, LSE, Tesco: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-06-14T06:40:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/london-stock-exchange-mwb-group-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  Futures on the FTSE 100 Index expiring in June climbed 0.4
percent at 7:39 a.m. in  London  today. The gauge gained 7.66
points, or 0.1 percent, to 5,773.46 yesterday, the FTSE All-
Share Index rose 0.1 percent and Ireland’s ISEQ advanced 0.8
percent.  Avis Europe Plc (AVE)  : The company agreed to be acquired
by Avis Budget Group Inc. for 636 million pounds ($1.04 billion)
or 315 pence a share. The stock rose 0.8 percent to 196.6 pence.  Carphone Warehouse Group Plc (CPW)  : The company said
earnings before interest and taxes for the year ended March 31
rose 67 percent to 63.3 million pounds from a year earlier as
its share of profit from Best Buy Co.’s U.S. mobile operations
more than doubled. The stock rose 3 percent to 398.5 pence.  Glencore International Plc (GLEN LN): The world’s biggest
publicly traded commodities trader reported a 47 percent
increase in first-quarter net income adjusted for exceptional.
Separately, Glencore made an initial agreement to buy CST Mining
Group Ltd.’s Peruvian copper project for $475 million. The
shares rose 2.8 percent to 523.4 pence.  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  : TMX Group Inc.
said its board will review Maple Group Acquisition Corp.’s
takeover offer for the Canadian exchange operator. Maple
earlier said TMX shareholders must vote against a takeover bid
from LSE on June 30 for Maple’s rival plan to proceed. LSE’s
stock rose 0.6 percent to 949 pence.  MWB Group Holdings Plc (MWB)  : Regus Plc said it has
withdrawn its offer to acquire MWB Business Exchange Plc. MWB
Business Exchange has urged shareholders to accept a rival offer
from MWB Group Holdings, which manages hotels, offices and
retail stores, to buy the 28 percent of the company it doesn’t
already own. MWB Group shares fell 2.8 percent to 44 pence.  Royal Bank of Scotland Plc (RBS LN): General Electric Co.’s
 GE Capital  is in discussions to buy Lombard Vehicle Management,
one of the U.K.’s largest car and van leasing companies, from
RBS, Sky News reported, without saying where it got the
information. RBS shares fell 0.1 percent to 40.57 pence.  Tesco Plc (TSCO)  : The U.K.’s largest grocer reported
first-quarter sales growth that missed analyst estimates amid
“constrained demand” for general merchandise.  U.K. same-store sales rose 1 percent, excluding gasoline
and including value-added tax. That compares to the median
analyst estimate of 1.5 percent and the fourth quarter’s 0.2
percent increase. The shares rose 0.2 percent to 407.2 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
